>
  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6 italic text-gray-300">Two hosts play through Gears of War: Ultimate Edition in co-op on <strong class="text-cyan-400">Hardcore difficulty</strong> (for achievement purposes). The remaster is praised for its visuals and stable 60fps — a significant improvement over the original 360 version. The hosts note a recurring issue where cutscenes reset the framerate to 30fps until the next death. This is a full-game run covering all five acts.</p>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">General Observations</h2>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Weapon variety</strong> is limited compared to Halo or CoD: the core loadout consists of the Lancer (chainsaw rifle), Hammerburst (semi-auto), Gnasher (shotgun), and Longshot (sniper). Hosts consider the <strong class="text-cyan-400">Hammerburst the worst weapon in any FPS</strong>.</li>
    <li>The <strong class="text-cyan-400">active reload system</strong> rewards precise timing with boosted damage; botching it jams your weapon — a common frustration throughout.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">COG tags</strong> (collectibles) are scattered throughout. The hosts attempt to find all 30 for the associated achievement, occasionally backtracking when they spot the icon.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Jack</strong> (the support drone) opens locked doors throughout the campaign. Sections requiring Jack to breach doors often double as ambush setups.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Chainsaw executions</strong> with the Lancer are frequent but sometimes unreliable — the enemy can counter-chainsaw you if the timing is close.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Act 1: Ashes</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Prison / Guards Quarters (Opening)</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Two route options at the start: Guards Quarters or Prison Blocks. Hosts go through the Guards Quarters.</li>
    <li>First enemies encountered — basic Locust Drones ("groundmen") emerging from emergence holes.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Turret enemies (Troika gunners):</strong> Shooting them in the head does nothing — aim for the <strong class="text-cyan-400">torso</strong>.</li>
    <li>A <strong class="text-cyan-400">Boomer</strong> appears early; large, slow enemy that fires explosive rounds. Can be chainsawed once weakened.</li>
    <li>The squad (Delta) reunites with Cole Train and Baird here.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">House of Sovereigns</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Multi-floor building with Locust on walls and ceilings, including <strong class="text-cyan-400">Wretches</strong> ("minimon") — small, fast melee enemies that climb surfaces. Easy to punch or melee.</li>
    <li>Hammer of Dawn used against enemies in an open courtyard section — requires clear sky and a lock-on. Works fast once the satellite acquires.</li>
    <li>COG tags found on several dead soldiers throughout the building.</li>
    <li>Cole Train (AI) tends to sprint into danger and get downed frequently.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Act 2: Nightfall</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Tomb of the Unknowns</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Urban ruins; mix of Drones and Boomers.</li>
    <li>A <strong class="text-cyan-400">Berserker</strong> (blind, female Locust) is introduced: immune to conventional weapons. Must be <strong class="text-cyan-400">lured outside</strong> for Hammer of Dawn exposure. She smashes through walls — let her chase you to an open-sky area, then triangulate and fire. Aim for her belly/front when she charges.</li>
    <li>Important: Hammer of Dawn <strong class="text-cyan-400">does not work indoors</strong> — you need clear sky for the satellite uplink.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Embry Square / Fenix Estate Exterior</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Long outdoor section fighting through streets toward Marcus's childhood home.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Torque Bow enemies</strong> appear — they fire explosive bolts that stick to surfaces and players. Kill them fast or roll away from tagged positions.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Flame Drones</strong> are standard Drones carrying a flamethrower — engage at range.</li>
    <li>Multiple Boomers defending approaches; Boom Shot (their dropped weapon) is useful but limited ammo.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Fenix Estate (Interior)</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Marcus's family mansion — multiple floors, wine cellar, weight room.</li>
    <li>COG tags hidden inside a <strong class="text-cyan-400">desk</strong> (use chainsaw on the desk to reveal).</li>
    <li>Another Berserker encounter occurs here; lure her to the greenhouse skylight for Hammer of Dawn.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Act 3: Belly of the Beast</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Underground / Krill Sections</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Enter the Locust underground network.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Krill (bats)</strong> are introduced: swarms that kill instantly in darkness. You must stay within <strong class="text-cyan-400">UV spotlight coverage</strong> — either from fixed lights or a mounted UV turret on a vehicle.</li>
    <li>Key tip: <strong class="text-cyan-400">turn on electricity</strong> at junction boxes to power static UV lights and keep paths safe.</li>
    <li>Vehicle section: one player drives while the other operates the UV turret. Hosts recommend calling out enemy positions as clock directions.</li>
    <li>The fuel station must be activated to progress — find the generator/valve before entering the dark zone.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Minecart Section</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>COG tags found on ledges above the main path — risky to grab.</li>
    <li>The minecart ride involves shooting enemies while moving on rails. Some enemies run on the tracks — they die instantly if hit by the cart.</li>
    <li>Two separate cart controls need to be activated by splitting up.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Act 4: The Long Road Home</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Lethia Imulsion Facility / Factory</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Industrial interior; emergence holes spawn Drones continuously until sealed.</li>
    <li>A <strong class="text-cyan-400">mounted Troika</strong> covers a key corridor — flank from the opposite side rather than engaging directly.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Bloodmounts</strong> appear (Drones riding beasts) — target the rider first.</li>
    <li>Gas canister mechanic: shoot canisters to create explosions against clustered enemies.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">East Barricade Academy</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Enemies use multiple floors — watch for fire from above.</li>
    <li>A <strong class="text-cyan-400">sniper nest</strong> covers the courtyard. The Longshot is the best counter at range.</li>
    <li>COG tags in this area are on upper-floor ledges.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Train Approach</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Linear outdoor section; Reavers (flying Locust on winged creatures) attack from the air. Use the Troika turret to shoot them down.</li>
    <li>Hosts strongly recommend getting on the turret — trying to fight Reavers on foot is very difficult on Hardcore.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Act 5: Desperation</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Fenix Research Facility</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>The section with <strong class="text-cyan-400">rotating valve puzzles</strong> — each player turns a valve simultaneously to unlock doors.</li>
    <li>More Torque Bow Drones in tight corridors — prioritize them.</li>
    <li>Large emergence hole spawns a sustained wave; recommended to hold a chokepoint doorway.</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Bridge / Final Approach</h3>
  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Extended combat across an open bridge. Boomers on both flanks.</li>
    <li>A <strong class="text-cyan-400">Brumak</strong> (giant Locust war machine) appears as the final boss:
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
        <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Phase 1:</strong> Shoot the <strong class="text-cyan-400">weapons/arms</strong> to disable its rocket pods and chain gun.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Phase 2:</strong> Shoot the <strong class="text-cyan-400">legs</strong> to expose the underside.</li>
        <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Final phase:</strong> Target the <strong class="text-cyan-400">driver in the cockpit</strong> (visible on top). The Boom Shot is highly effective here.</li>
        <li>The Hammer of Dawn does not appear to be usable under the bridge — get to an open area.</li>
        <li>Hosts went down multiple times during this encounter on Hardcore.</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Achievement Notes</h2>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Hardcore difficulty completion</strong> — unlocks a difficulty-related achievement.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">COG tags:</strong> 30 total across the game. Hosts collected approximately 22 by end. Missed tags can be replayed per chapter.</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Chainsaw / melee kills</strong> — a chainsaw kill achievement is possible; hosts attempt to chainsaw frequently.</li>
    <li>Combat achievements accumulate naturally on a full playthrough.</li>
  </ul>

  <hr class="my-8 border-gray-700" />

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300 mt-8">Overall Impressions</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">The hosts enjoy the first half of the game but find the second half increasingly frustrating on Hardcore, citing inconsistent chainsaw collision, frequent curb-stomp executions by enemies, and the framerate dropping after every cutscene. The remaster visuals hold up well — described as looking like a modern game despite the 2005 original. The hosts plan to continue with Gears of War 2–5 and Judgment.</p>
</BlogPostLayout>
